---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import { profile, template } from '@/settings'
import ProfilePictures from '@/assets/profile_pictures.jpg'
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'

const { fullName, title, institute } = profile
---

<Layout description="Zeyu (Alban) Li, Cornell Ph.D. building reliable applied AI for scientific R&D, grounded in a decade of hands-on materials and nucleic-acid research.">
	<!-- Hero Section -->
	<section class='flex flex-col items-center text-center py-8 sm:py-12'>
		<Image
			class='mask mask-circle size-48 mb-8 ring-4 ring-primary/10'
			src={ProfilePictures}
			alt={`Profile picture of ${fullName}`}
		/>
		<h1 class='text-2xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-primary'>Zeyu (Alban) Li</h1>
		<h2 class='text-sm sm:text-lg lg:text-xl text-primary mb-2 font-medium px-2'>Ph.D., Cornell University <span class="mx-2 opacity-50">|</span> Scientist-Engineer</h2>
		<p class='text-sm sm:text-lg font-semibold text-base-content/70 mb-8'>
			Applied AI for Scientific R&D <span class="mx-2 opacity-50">|</span> Materials Scientist <span class="mx-2 opacity-50">|</span> Nucleic Acid Scientist
		</p>
		
		<!-- CTA Buttons - Primary action with optimized visibility -->
		<div class='flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center'>
			<a href={`${template.base}/ai`} class='btn btn-accent'>
				<span class='font-semibold tracking-wide'>Applied AI</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${template.base}/research`} class='btn btn-primary'>
				<span class='font-semibold tracking-wide'>Scientific R&D</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${template.base}/cv`} class='btn btn-outline btn-primary'>
				Download CV
			</a>
			<button onclick="contact_modal.showModal()" class='btn btn-outline btn-primary'>
				Get in Touch
			</button>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- About Section -->
	<section class='py-8 sm:py-12 border-t border-base-300'>
		<h2 class='text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-10 text-primary fade-in-up'>About</h2>
		<div class='prose max-w-none prose-base sm:prose-lg'>
			<p class='text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed !mb-8 text-base-content fade-in-up'>
				I build reliable AI for scientific R&D, grounded in a decade of hands-on materials and nucleic-acid research and the experimental judgment to keep that AI trustworthy.<br /><span class="inline-block mt-3 bg-primary text-white px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Now available for full-time roles.</span>
			</p>

			<h3 class='flex items-center gap-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-8 pt-8 border-t border-base-300 text-primary fade-in-up'><span class='w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded'></span>Academic & Research Background</h3>

			<div class="space-y-12 mb-8">
				<!-- Cornell University -->
				<div class="fade-in-up">
					<div class="mb-4">
						<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary">Cornell University</h4>
						<p class="text-base font-medium text-base-content/80">Ph.D. | M.S. | M.Eng. | Biological & Environmental Engineering</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="space-y-3">
						<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-1 sm:gap-4">
							<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary pt-0.5">Lab</span>
							<span class="text-base text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed"><a href="https://albanli0314.github.io/LuolabCornell/" class="hover:underline text-primary">DNA Materials Lab</a> (<a href="https://cals.cornell.edu/people/dan-luo" class="hover:underline text-primary">Prof. Dan Luo</a>)</span>
						</div>
						
						<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-1 sm:gap-4">
							<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary pt-0.5">Concentration</span>
							<span class="text-base text-secondary font-medium leading-relaxed">Materials Science, Biological Engineering, Bioenvironmental Engineering</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Hong Kong Baptist University -->
				<div class="fade-in-up">
					<div class="mb-4">
						<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary">Hong Kong Baptist University</h4>
						<p class="text-base font-medium text-base-content/80">B.Sc. | Chemistry (Hons) | Computer Science (Minor)</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="space-y-3">
						<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-1 sm:gap-4">
							<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary pt-0.5">Lab</span>
							<span class="text-base text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed"><a href="https://renkangning.wixsite.com/rengroup" class="hover:underline text-primary">Micro-fabrication & Surface Materials Lab</a> (<a href="https://chem.hkbu.edu.hk/ren" class="hover:underline text-primary">Prof. Kangning Ren</a>)</span>
						</div>
						
						<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-1 sm:gap-4">
							<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary pt-0.5">Research</span>
							<span class="text-base text-secondary font-medium leading-relaxed">Micro-fabrication and Surface Materials Engineering</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		<h3 class='flex items-center gap-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-8 pt-8 border-t border-base-300 text-primary fade-in-up'><span class='w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded'></span>Applied AI</h3>

		<p class='text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 text-base-content fade-in-up'>
			Beyond using AI, I build it: agents, retrieval, and evaluation systems for scientific and high-stakes work, engineered to stay reliable and grounded in real evidence.
		</p>

		<ul class='list-disc list-outside ml-0 space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80 !mb-8 fade-in-up'>
			<li>
				<strong>Agentic AI for research:</strong> I built Research Harness, an agentic framework that turns LLMs into reliable research assistants, with built-in checks, evidence-aware guardrails, and a trail from every output back to its source data. The work became my first-author paper at the ICML AI for Science Workshop 2026.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>AI applications I've shipped:</strong> I design and deploy retrieval systems and real-time voice agents, from Resonance, which helps researchers find the right collaborators, to ER Companion, a multilingual ER-intake agent that won the Cornell AI Health Hackathon.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Reliability is the difference:</strong> I build the evaluation and guardrail layers most AI work skips, and I draw on a decade in the lab to catch when a model is confidently wrong.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Teaching it forward:</strong> As a Cornell co-instructor and guest lecturer, I teach building agents, prompt and context engineering, and how to put AI to work in real scientific workflows.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<div class='border-t border-base-300 pt-8 mb-8'>
			<h3 class='flex items-center gap-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-8 text-primary fade-in-up'><span class='w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded'></span>Key Achievements</h3>
			<div class='grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6'>
				<div class='card bg-base-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 border-l-2 border-accent stagger-card'>
					<div class='card-body p-4'>
						<h4 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-primary'>Large-Scale Field Deployment</h4>
						<p class='text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80'>
							Led an <strong>11 km²</strong> field deployment of DNA-barcoded microparticle tracers for a <strong>U.S. Department of Defense (DoD)</strong> funded project; achieved qPCR detection <strong>7 km</strong> downstream from <strong>&lt;1 mg</strong> DNA release. <strong>First-author paper</strong> published on ACS ES&T (<strong>Top 5%</strong> Journal in Environmental Sciences)
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class='card bg-base-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 border-l-2 border-accent stagger-card'>
					<div class='card-body p-4'>
						<h4 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-primary'>Long-Lifetime Biocatalytic Composite</h4>
						<p class='text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80'>
							Co-engineered a covalent DNA-PEG hydrogel-mesh composite (NucleoMesh) that withstands continuous enzymatic reaction conditions for <strong>100+ days</strong>, functioning as a reusable solid-phase biocatalyst for nucleic-acid manufacturing. <strong>Second-author paper</strong> in peer review at Nature Sustainability.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class='card bg-base-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 border-l-2 border-accent stagger-card'>
					<div class='card-body p-4'>
						<h4 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-primary'>Functional Materials Engineering</h4>
						<p class='text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80'>
							Developed a DNA–Al³⁺ hydrogel composite that is <strong>3D-printable</strong> and <strong>self-healing</strong> for structural repair applications. <strong>Co-First author</strong> paper published ACADIA 2024 (Premier Conference in Computational Design)
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class='card bg-base-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 border-l-2 border-accent stagger-card'>
					<div class='card-body p-4'>
						<h4 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-primary'>Leadership, Mentoring & Innovation</h4>
						<p class='text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80'>
							Co-authored <strong>5 publications</strong> and co-invented <strong>2 patents</strong>; coordinated collaborations across <strong>7 research groups</strong>. Mentored <strong>3 undergraduate researchers</strong> and served as Teaching Assistant/Co-instructor for <strong>7 university courses</strong>.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<h3 class='flex items-center gap-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-8 pt-8 border-t border-base-300 text-primary fade-in-up'><span class='w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded'></span>Value & Approach</h3>
		
		<div class='grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16'>
			<div class='card bg-base-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300 fade-in-up'>
				<div class='card-body pt-3 pb-4'>
					<h4 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-primary'>For Materials Industry</h4>
					<ul class='list-disc list-outside ml-0 space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80'>
						<li>
							<strong class="block mb-1">Cross-Disciplinary "Translator"</strong>
							I translate ambiguous applications into precise material specifications. I bridge technical gaps by synthesizing expertise across life sciences, engineering, and design—a skill honed through leading complex, interdisciplinary initiatives.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="block mb-1">Independent Execution</strong>
							I back up strategy with hands-on execution—a capability grounded in my experience independently navigating the full R&D cycle, from polymer fabrication and characterization to the delivery of validated, real-world prototypes.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class='card bg-base-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300 fade-in-up'>
				<div class='card-body pt-3 pb-4'>
					<h4 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-primary'>For Biotech Industry</h4>
					<ul class='list-disc list-outside ml-0 space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-base-content/80'>
						<li>
							<strong class="block mb-1">The "Chemist's Lens"</strong>
							I bring a material-driven perspective to biological engineering, unlocking scalability and cost-efficiency where traditional approaches struggle. This capability is rooted in treating DNA/RNA as functional macromolecules—applying polymer science to resolve fundamental formulation bottlenecks.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="block mb-1">Full-Stack Proficiency</strong>
							I deliver technical oversight that bridges the gap between R&D concepts and reliable product delivery. This capability stems from my mastery of the end-to-end workflow—enforcing strict process controls from upstream enzymatic synthesis to downstream purification and quantification.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class='mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center'>
			<a href={`${template.base}/ai`} class='btn btn-accent btn-lg'>
				<span class='font-semibold tracking-wide'>Explore Applied AI →</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${template.base}/research`} class='btn btn-primary btn-lg'>
				<span class='font-semibold tracking-wide'>Explore Scientific R&D →</span>
			</a>
		</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
